    Demo Case 03 - In Progress / General Inquiry / Medium priority
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the THIRD of the 10-case demo dataset; together with
    cases 01 and 02 (Draft and Open General Inquiry, which precede it
    in the General Inquiry lifecycle) and cases 04 through 10 (which
    cover the remaining statuses across both case types), it satisfies
    the AAP requirement (Section 0.7.4) of "at least 10 demo cases
    across all six statuses and both case types," and contributes to
    the dataset matrix:

        Case 01 - Draft       / General Inquiry
        Case 02 - Open        / General Inquiry
        Case 03 - In Progress / General Inquiry / Medium    ## THIS FILE
        Case 04 - Pending     / General Inquiry / High
        Case 05 - Resolved    / General Inquiry
        Case 06 - Closed      / General Inquiry
        Case 07 - Open        / Complaint
        Case 08 - In Progress / Complaint
        Case 09 - Resolved    / Complaint
        Case 10 - Closed      / Complaint

    The 10-case dataset thus exercises:
      * Every one of the six statuses (Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending,
        Resolved, Closed) - this case occupies the In Progress slot for
        the General Inquiry case type. It is paired with case 08, which
        occupies the In Progress slot for the Complaint case type.
        Together cases 03 and 08 cover the In Progress status across
        both case types.
      * Both case types (General Inquiry and Complaint) - case 03 is on
        the General Inquiry side; case 08 is the Complaint counterpart.
      * Multiple priorities (Low, Medium, High, Critical) - this case
        contributes the Medium bar to the all_cases_by_priority chart
        (paired with cases 02 and 05, which are also Medium).
      * The polymorphic case_party UI Policy (BOTH Person and
        Organization branches) - this case is one of the few demo
        cases (along with the dataset's Person+Organization pair
        case) that has BOTH a Person-type party and an Organization-
        type party, exercising both branches of the
        x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields UI Policy on the
        case_party form.
      * The In Progress -> Resolved RESOLVE-BLOCKER guard - this case
        is the CANONICAL resolve-blocker test case for the entire
        scoped application (see "Key insights" #2 below).

    Lifecycle position - WHY In Progress / General Inquiry / Medium is
    meaningful:
      A General Inquiry case that has reached In Progress status has
      traversed:
        Draft -> Open -> In Progress
      The case has been opened (assigned to a group on the Draft -> Open
      transition) and assigned to a specific agent (assigned to an agent
      on the Open -> In Progress transition); the agent is actively
      investigating the case. Per AAP Section 0.5.5's transition matrix:
        - The Open -> In Progress transition is gated by
          validate_inprogress_transition: assigned_agent must be
          populated AND must be a member of assigned_group; the
          validate_assigned_agent_membership business rule re-verifies
          group membership at every Before-Update.
        - The In Progress -> Pending transition is unconditional but
          REQUIRES pending_reason to be populated (case 04 demonstrates
          the post-transition state).
        - The In Progress -> Resolved transition is gated by
          validate_resolved_transition: ALL linked x_[scope]_case_task
          records must have status=Closed; otherwise the verbatim
          blocking error "All tasks must be closed before resolving
          this case." is surfaced on the form (per AAP Section 0.7.4).
      This case occupies the In Progress side of those gates: both
      assignment fields are populated, pending_reason is absent (this
      case is NOT in Pending), and per the seed script's task table
      this case carries an Open child task that BLOCKS any attempt to
      transition it to Resolved. The Medium priority is the canonical
      "ordinary case" priority - elevated above Low (no urgency) but
      not yet reaching High or Critical thresholds.

