    Authoring rules honored (per AAP Sections 0.7.1 / 0.7.2 and the
    agent prompt's ten authoring rules):

      Rule 1 - Synthetic only (AAP Section 0.7.2 NO-PII clause):
        subject       = "Demo case 03: In Progress (General Inquiry)"
        description   = "Synthetic In Progress case actively assigned
                         to demo agent." (no PII; the wording emphasizes
                         the lifecycle position - actively-worked, agent
                         assigned)
        requester_name  = "Synthetic Requester Three" (synthetic
                          identifier using the literal word "Synthetic"
                          plus the SPELLED-OUT numeral "Three" for the
                          requester, NOT a real person's name;
                          consistent with the peer convention used by
                          cases 04 through 10 - SPELLED-OUT word for
                          the requester_name)
        requester_email = "requester-3@example.invalid"
                          (RFC 2606 / BCP 32 reserved .invalid TLD never
                          resolves to a real domain; the local part uses
                          the NUMERAL "3" matching the file numbering -
                          consistent with the peer convention used by
                          cases 04-10's NUMERAL convention for the email
                          local part versus the SPELLED-OUT word for
                          the requester_name field)

      Rule 2 - No auto-number override:
        The <number/> element is intentionally absent. The auto-number
        engine defined in ../../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case.xml
        generates a CASE0000001-format value on insert per AAP Section
        0.5.7 (the "number" row of the case schema specifies "Auto-
        number" with format CASE0000001 and Read-only constraint).

      Rule 3 - Auto-set opened_date (NO explicit override):
        The <opened_date/> element is intentionally absent. The
        set_opened_date Before-Insert business rule at
        ../../business_rules/x_[scope]_set_opened_date.xml fires on
        insert and sets opened_date = gs.nowDateTime(). On a fresh
        PDI import this yields an opened_date "now," which is correct
        for this In Progress case because:
          * It is NOT used to compute avg_time_to_close (which excludes
            non-Closed cases via the status=Closed filter).
          * It IS appropriate for the case to appear "fresh" in the
            cases_opened_30d count (an actively-worked case is still
            recently opened).
        Pattern matches cases 02 (Open General Inquiry), 04 (Pending
        General Inquiry), 05 (Resolved General Inquiry), 07 (Open
        Complaint), 08 (In Progress Complaint), and 09 (Resolved
        Complaint), which also do NOT need explicit opened_date
        overrides. Only cases 06 (Closed General Inquiry) and 10
        (Closed Complaint) carry explicit opened_date and closed_date
        overrides because they are the only inputs to the
        avg_time_to_close widget.

      Rule 4 - No closed_date in In Progress:
        The <closed_date/> element is intentionally absent. Per AAP
        Section 0.5.5 the set_closed_date business rule fires only on
        Resolved -> Closed update, NOT on direct insert with status =
        In Progress. In Progress cases by definition have not been
        Closed (In Progress is an actively-worked state, not a terminal
        state), so closed_date MUST remain null. The avg_time_to_close
        report filters on status=Closed and ignores non-Closed records,
        so this case correctly does NOT appear in that widget.

      Rule 5 - Both assignments populated, NO pending_reason:
        assigned_group = "x_[scope]_demo_team"  (mandatory because the
                         case had to traverse Open -> In Progress, and
                         assigned_group is required at Open per AAP
                         Section 0.5.5; the value persists through all
                         subsequent statuses)
        assigned_agent = "x_[scope]_demo_agent"  (mandatory for In
                         Progress per AAP Section 0.5.5; the demo agent
                         is also a member of x_[scope]_demo_team per
                         the seed script's group-membership creation,
                         satisfying the validate_assigned_agent_membership
                         business rule's pre-update guard and the
                         validate_inprogress_transition subflow's
                         pre-condition)
        pending_reason = (absent)  (NOT applicable to In Progress
                         status; pending_reason is set ONLY when status
                         is Pending, set by the validate_pending_transition
                         subflow on the In Progress -> Pending transition,
                         and cleared by the
                         clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress business
                         rule on the Pending -> In Progress transition.
                         For this case (In Progress), pending_reason is
                         absent / null).

      Rule 6 - Choice value precision:
        type     = "General Inquiry"  (exactly as registered in
                   ../../choices/sys_choice_case_type.xml; the FIRST of
                   the two case types; capital G and capital I
