                      the Update Set engine for scope-package binding.
        Note: the source attribute value "x_[scope]" matches what every
        peer file uses; it is the scope's <source> field, NOT the
        scoped application's sys_update_name. This is the convention
        used consistently across the project's Update Set artifacts
        (cases 04/05/06/07/08/09/10, all sys_user_*, sys_user_group_*,
        sys_user_has_role_* records use the same convention).

      Rule 9 - Idempotency anchor:
        The case's idempotent key is <subject> =
        "Demo case 03: In Progress (General Inquiry)". The companion
        seed script ../../scripts/seed_demo_data.js ensureCase() helper
        queries x_[scope]_case by subject BEFORE inserting; the
        action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE" attribute on the inner <x_[scope]_case>
        element ensures the same behavior at Update Set import time.
        Both the action attribute and the deterministic sys_id make
        re-imports on a fresh PDI byte-identical and collision-free.

      Rule 10 - Scoped Update Set XML conventions:
        Root element:  <record_update table="x_[scope]_case">
        Inner element: <x_[scope]_case action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"> for
                       idempotent re-import per AAP Section 0.7.1
                       round-trip-verification gate (Validation Gate 7).
        UTF-8 encoding declared in XML prolog.
        Element ordering: alphabetical (matching the established peer
        convention used by sys_user_*, sys_user_group_*,
        sys_user_has_role_*, role records, cases 04/05/06/07/08/09/10,
        and dictionary entries across the scoped Update Set).
        Unix-style line endings (LF) per AAP file authoring conventions.

    Source-side semantic reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported)
    per AAP Section 0.8.1:
      acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java
        ArkCase's CaseFile JPA entity declares ~80 fields including
        cm_case_status (the source for our <status>), cm_case_priority
        (the source for our <priority>), cm_case_type (the source for
        our <type>), cm_case_title (the source for our <subject>),
        cm_case_details (Lob; the source for our <description>), and
        the assignment fields (assignee, owner) that informed the
        assigned_agent / assigned_group semantics. The ServiceNow
        target collapses ArkCase's ~80 fields to the user-prompt's
        12-field schema (number, type, status, priority, subject,
        description, opened_date, closed_date, assigned_group,
        assigned_agent, requester_name, requester_email - plus the
        optional pending_reason). ArkCase's ChangeCaseFileStateService
        Java class (which managed status transitions and is the source
        of the In Progress -> Resolved validation semantics) is
        replaced in this POC by Flow Designer's
        general_inquiry_state_machine.xml flow plus its
        validate_resolved_transition subflow and the
        x_[scope]_CaseTransitionValidator script include (which
        encapsulates the "all tasks closed" check that THIS CASE'S
        Open child task is designed to fail). ArkCase's
        CaseFileTasksService (which aggregated tasks for a case in
        the Java source) is the conceptual ancestor of the
        validate_resolved_transition subflow's GlideRecord query
        against x_[scope]_case_task.

    Validation hooks (per the agent prompt):
      - The XML well-formedness check (xmllint with no-output flag)
        returns zero errors.
      - No-PII grep returns zero matches against (john|jane|smith|doe|
        @gmail|@yahoo|@outlook|@hotmail|\.com|\.org|\.net) - the
        synthetic identifiers ("Synthetic Requester Three",
        "requester-3@example.invalid", "x_[scope]_demo_agent",
        "x_[scope]_demo_team") do not include any PII tokens.
      - Choice-value validation: <type>General Inquiry</type>,
        <status>In Progress</status>, <priority>Medium</priority> -
        capital G/I, capital I/P (with embedded ASCII space), capital
        M respectively.
      - Anti-pattern validation: NO <number>, NO <opened_date>,
        NO <closed_date>, NO <pending_reason> elements present.
      - Sys-id-literal validation: only ONE <sys_id> element (the
        case's own primary key); NO sys_id literals appear in any
        cross-reference field (all references use display_value
        attributes with stable lookup keys).
      - Scope-placeholder validation: the literal `[scope]` placeholder
        is preserved verbatim in the sys_class_name, sys_update_name,
        all reference values, and the file path; the PDI auto-assigns
        the actual concrete scope id at App Engine Studio creation
        time, and the Update-Set apply-time substitution propagates
        consistently across all bracketed placeholders.

    Key insights (per the agent prompt):
      1. Demo case 03 is the canonical In Progress case for the
         General Inquiry flow. It exercises both assigned_group and
         assigned_agent populated, demonstrating the post-Open ->
         In Progress transition state where the case is actively
         being investigated by the assigned agent.
      2. THIS CASE IS THE CANONICAL RESOLVE-BLOCKER TEST CASE for
         the entire scoped application. Per the seed script's task
         table, this case carries TWO child tasks:
           "Demo task 01: Investigate request scope"  (status=Open)
           "Demo task 02: Initial review complete"    (status=Closed)
         The presence of "Demo task 01" with status=Open means any
         attempt to transition this case from In Progress to Resolved
         MUST be blocked by the validate_resolved_transition subflow
         with the verbatim error message "All tasks must be closed
         before resolving this case." (per AAP Section 0.7.4).
         Validation Gate 2 (Workflow) explicitly tests this behavior:
           Step 1: Attempt to set this case status to Resolved while
                   "Demo task 01" is Open. Expected result: blocking
                   error surfaced on form; transition denied.
           Step 2: Manually close "Demo task 01" (set its status to
                   Closed). Re-attempt the In Progress -> Resolved
                   transition. Expected result: transition succeeds;
                   case status = Resolved.
         No other case in the 10-case dataset is the canonical input
         for this gate; this case alone is the canonical
         resolve-blocker test.
      3. The status "In Progress" has a SPACE, not a hyphen, not an
         underscore, not concatenated. The exact choice value is
         "In Progress" per AAP Section 0.5.7 and
         ../../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml. Common mistakes to
         avoid: "in-progress", "InProgress", "in_progress",
         "IN_PROGRESS" - all of these would FAIL choice-value
         validation against the registered choice list.
      4. The <assigned_agent> reference uses
         display_value="x_[scope]_demo_agent" and resolves by
         user_name lookup against sys_user. The element value is the
         same string as the display_value (NOT a sys_id literal). This
         matches the convention established by the demo agent's
         primary-key record at
         ../users/sys_user_x_[scope]_demo_agent.xml and the peer case
         records.
      5. The validation chain that allows In Progress: (1) the case
         has assigned_group set (was set on Draft -> Open transition),
         (2) the case has assigned_agent set (was set on Open -> In
         Progress transition), (3) the agent is a member of the group
         (validated by the validate_assigned_agent_membership business
         rule and re-validated on every Before-Update). All three
         conditions hold for this case.
      6. Demo case 03 has BOTH party types - Person AND Organization
         - per the seed script's party table:
           Person-type Requester party referencing the demo manager
           Organization-type Respondent party referencing
             "Synthetic Org Alpha"
         This case is one of the few demo cases that exercises BOTH
         branches of the polymorphic case_party UI Policy on the
         case_party form (the
         x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields UI Policy shows the
         person reference field when party_type=Person AND shows the
         organization reference field when party_type=Organization).
      7. The case appears in the Agent Workspace dashboard's "My Open
         Cases" list. The list filter is "status NOT IN (Resolved,
         Closed) AND assigned_agent = javascript:gs.getUserID()". In
         Progress is NOT in the (Resolved, Closed) exclusion set, and
         the demo agent is the assigned_agent; when the demo agent
         impersonates and opens the dashboard, this case shows in
         the list. This case also populates one of the two In Progress
         slices in the case_count_by_status donut and one of the two
         In Progress bars in the all_cases_by_status bar chart
         (paired with case 08 Complaint In Progress).
      8. The avg_time_to_close widget excludes this case. In Progress
         cases are not Closed, so they do not contribute to the
         average-time-to-close calculation. Only cases 06 (Closed
         General Inquiry) and 10 (Closed Complaint) drive that
         widget. This case does, however, contribute to the
         cases_opened_30d single-score widget (since the
         set_opened_date business rule auto-sets opened_date to "now"
         at insert time, placing this case in the 30-day window) and
         to the case_count_by_status donut (In Progress slice).
      9. The In Progress -> Pending transition is testable USING this
         case as the input. If a case_agent (demo agent) sets this
         case status to Pending via the form, the
         validate_pending_transition subflow prompts for
         pending_reason and persists the chosen value. The
         POST-transition state (where pending_reason has been
         populated) is demonstrated by sibling case 04. This case
         and case 04 thus form a paired demonstration of the
         In Progress <-> Pending transition cycle.
     10. The literal "[scope]" placeholder is preserved verbatim
         throughout the file - in the sys_class_name, sys_update_name,
         table attribute, inner element name, all cross-reference
         text values, and the file path. The PDI substitutes the
         auto-assigned concrete scope id at apply-time;
         pre-substituting here would break the substitution mechanism.
-->
<record_update table="x_[scope]_case">
